 IN THE CITY
				 																																																	 In a bid to groom tennis talent in the city, the Asian Tennis Federation and All India Tennis Association will run a joint year-long programme. It will be run by the affiliated units of Bengal and have Akhtar Ali as chief adviser. A trial was recently held to select the players for the programme.				 																																																	 Abhishek Mukherjee, a certified International Tennis Federation official, has been selected to officiate at the Beijing Olympics. He has earlier officiated at the Wimbledon for three consecutive years. 				 																																																	Abhishek is also due to officiate in major tournaments like the Hyundai Hopman Cup in Perth (December 29-January 3, 2008) and Australian Open (January 10-23, 2008). 				 																																																	 The grasscourt national tennis championship will be held at South Club from December 17-22. The meet assumes significance in that the winner will get a wildcard entry for the ATP Chennai Open. 				 																																																	 HDFC General Insurance beat British Deputy High Commission B 3-0 in the Mercantile five-a-side soccer meet at Rangers Club on Wednesday.				 																																																	OTHER RESULTS  Bharat Petroleum bt Wipro 3-1; The Park bt SAB Miller 3-2; Transworld bt HT Media 5-1; Taj Bengal bt HDFC Bank 2-1.				 																																																	FOOTBALL: 5-a-side Mercantile meet at Rangers Club from 6.30pm.
